I happen to find there is a large memory consumption when I load a model with dynet_load_model. The workflow of my code is like:

```
Model m;
m.add_parameter(...); // add several parameter
for (unsigned iter = 0; iter < max_iter; ++iter) {
   // training m
   if (best development score achieved) { save_dynet_model(path, m); }
}
load_dynet_model(path, m);
// perform testing.
```

I see line 201 in tensor.cc:
```
  device->allocate_tensor(mem_pool, *this)
```
which means each time we load a model (or more exactly, a tensor), no matter whether the memory has been allocated, we still want some memory from the pool. It ok if the model is small but when the model is large, doubling the memory is fatal.

